# Build-context excludes for BOTH images. The backend and frontend builds use the
# REPOSITORY ROOT as their context (docker build -f infra/docker/Dockerfile.* .),
# and a .dockerignore is read from the context root — so this file, not the one
# under infra/docker, is the one that takes effect.
#
# The load-bearing line is **/application-local.yml: .gitignore treats it as a local
# secret store, and Gradle's processResources would otherwise package it straight
# into the boot jar that ships in the PUBLIC runtime image. Scoped COPY does not stop
# that — only excluding it from the context does.

.git
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/build
**/.gradle
**/.angular
**/out-tsc
**/coverage
**/playwright-report
**/test-results
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/application-local.yml
**/*.pem
**/secrets/
**/*.tfstate
**/*.tfstate.*
**/*.tfvars
**/.DS_Store
**/*.log
**/.idea
**/.vscode
